for work this morning.

65
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:16,530
I had to tell Mr. Burns
you had violent diarrhea.

66
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:20,070
Oh, couldn't you come up
with a less embarrassing lie?

67
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,430
But you did have violent diarrhea.

68
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:26,140
Nobody open the hallway closet
until I say it's okay.

69
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,960
[BOTH SHUDDERING]

70
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,040
Remember how you got home
last night, Dad?

71
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,490
Of course.

72
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:35,460
It was, uh, some kind of a light rail.

73
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,740
There's no light rail in Springfield.

74
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,880
Oh, won't anyone pretend
to believe me?

75
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,200
- I will, Dad.
- That's why you're my favorite.

76
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,730
All right, time for my favorite show.

77
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,070
MAN [ON TV]:
MTC: Monkey Trauma Center...

78
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,680
<i>...will not be seen tonight...</i>

79
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,160
Oh.

80
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,200
MAN: <i>...so we may present
this cheaper show.</i>

81
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:59,710
WOMAN [ON TV]:
<i>Taxicab Conversations.</i>

82
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,560
Hey, I read about this show
in <i>Teen Modern Maturity.</i>

83
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,100
