catch them at their most uninhibited.

84
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,880
That explains that.

85
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,820
[DISCO MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

86
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,670
[HUMMING]

87
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,520
Looks like somebody
got down tonight.

88
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:18,130
Disco Stu always gets down, baby.

89
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,320
Because when the beat is hot, the...

90
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,740
[SIGHS]

91
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,180
- Hey, can you keep a secret?
- What is it, hon?

92
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,970
I hate disco.

93
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:29,730
It's all I've talked about for so long,
people think I'm a one-note guy.

94
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,480
[SIGHS]

95
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,590
It's just getting harder, you know.

96
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,640
I had no idea Disco Stu
was so complex.

97
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,270
- How you doing?
- Talky thing, ain't you?

98
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,750
Another proud moment
for the Simpsons.

99
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,520
I don't remember anybody telling me
I was gonna be on TV.

100
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:50,740
- So, what do you do for a living?
- Oh, you know, I'm a guy at a place.

101
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:54,980
How'd you get such a crappy job?
You a convict or a junkie?

102
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,000
- Little of both. You got a family?
- Oh, yeah.

103
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:00,200
Wife and two or three kids.

104
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,180
Can't imagine my life without them.

105
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,180
Oh, you big fooler.

106
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,130
Pretending not to remember
so you could surprise us.

107
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,520
[CHUCKLES]

108
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,210
Yeah, I'm pretty great.

109
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,460
At the end of a hard day...

110
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:16,960
...there's no better feeling than coming
home to the people that you love.

111
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:20,740
- Oh, Homie.
- That is so sweet.

112
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,800
I had no idea, Dad.

113
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,410
I just assumed with all the stranglings,
you know...

114
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,270
That my family isn't the center
of my universe?

115
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,310
Are you nuts?

116
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,330
Then there's those other days...

117
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:35,850
...where you just wish
you never got married or had kids.

118
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,350
[GROANS]

119
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,580
One minute,
you're a carefree teenager...

120
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:44,040
...with dreams of being a rock star,
or a photographer for <i>Playboy...</i>

121
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,890
...then, bam,
some babe gets her claws in you...

122
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,640
Huh?

123
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,550
...and, boom, you got a bunch of kids
that always needs love.

124
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,320
[BOTH GASPING]

125
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:58,140
So whammo, you get stuck
in some boring job...

126
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:02,400
...where they don't let you play guitar
or take pictures of naked women.

127
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,700
And all you can do
is watch yourself get bald and fat...

128
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:10,170
...and kiss your dreams goodbye.

129
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:13,150
[SNORING]

130
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:16,910
Oh, I can't believe they took
<i>Monkey Trauma Center </i>off for this.

131
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,540
[SNORING]

132
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:24,020
<i>Lousy family.</i>

133
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:28,140
So I'm just some babe
who sank her claws into you.

134
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,940
- A hot babe.
- Oh!

135
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,070
Have you always resented us, Dad?

136
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,760
Oh, I don't resent you, sweetheart.

137
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:39,160
What I was trying to say,
and maybe I didn't use the right words...

138
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:43,090
...was that marriage is like a coffin
and each kid is another nail.

139
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,040
- But as coffins go...
- Please don't say anymore.

140
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,070
Sorry we ruined your life, Homer.

141
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,230
Hmph!

142
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,390
Oh, what have I done?

143
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,030
[ALARM WHISTLES]

144
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,050
- Get in.
- What?

145
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,800
Get in.

146
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,730
Hey, what's this suitcase for?

147
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,940
- Are we going on a trip?
- You are.

148
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,720
[LAUGHING]

149
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,120
[WHIMPERS]

150
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,620
Where are you taking me?

151
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,800
A place where you'll never be bothered
by your family again.

152
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,800
[GASPS]

153
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,960
Oh.

154
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,980
[WHIMPERS]

155
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,950
[SCREAMS]

156
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,730
Get out of the car, Homer.

157
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:36,270
You can't just leave me out here.
There's not another woman for miles.

158
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,880
Sorry, Dad.
Maybe now you'll appreciate us.

159
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,360
While you're spending the week at...

160
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,840
Rock 'n' Roll Fantasy Camp.

161
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,240
[HOMER GASPS]

162
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,630
The Rolling Stones' Rock 'n' Roll
Fantasy Camp.

163
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,870
But I thought
you guys were mad at me.

164
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:53,310
For once in my life, I'm confused.

165
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,730
We had a family meeting
and decided...

166
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,570
...that even though what you said
about us was incredibly thoughtless...

167
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,960
...and hurtful, you had a point.

168
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,570
- Damn straight.
- You work a job you don't like...

169
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,870
...so I'm able to be home with the kids.

170
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,650
And you take me places you hate like
museums, plays and the Olive Garden.

171
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,490
And even though you knew
I ratted you out to the IRS...

172
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,470
- ...you never busted me.
- You what?

173
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:18,760
So to say thank you
for all your sacrifices...

174
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:23,290
...we spent our family vacation fund
on something that's just for you.

175
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,620
- Do you like it?
- You guys are the best.

176
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,760
I love you. I love you. I love you...
Ugh, oh.

177
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:30,230
I'm okay.
I love you. I love you. I love you.

178
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,700
[OWL HOOTING]

179
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,990
Hey, what gives?
Where are all the rock stars?

180
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,310
I don't know,
but it's starting to get dark.

181
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,130
[GUITAR PLAYS NEARBY]

182
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,680
Huh, what was that?

183
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,410
Oh, it's getting closer.

184
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,790
- Hello, campers.
- How you doing?

185
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:58,650
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
It's Mick Jagger and Keith Richards.

186
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,000
[GROANS]

187
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,230
Welcome
to Rock 'n' Roll Fantasy Camp...

188
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:06,490
...where you'll experience
the complete rock 'n' roll lifestyle...

189
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,430
...without the lawsuits and STDs.

190
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:12,910
- Whoa! STDs!
- Now, you're all here for one reason...

191
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,270
- To rock!
- Who said that?

192
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,480
That's right, Otto. We're here to rock!

193
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,570
[ALL CHEERING]

194
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,200
So get a good night's sleep.

195
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:26,840
And remember rule number one,
there are no rules.

196
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,900
[ALL CHEERING]

197
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,790
Rule number two, no outside food.

198
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,300
Oh, what a gyp.

199
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,500
Hey, Mick, you gonna teach us
your cocksure strut?

200
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:39,070
Not today,
I got a ton of paperwork to catch up on.

201
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:43,070
Ah, tell me about it. At my job, we...
Oh, you're gone.

202
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,680
RICHARDS [ON PA]:
<i>Hey! Wake up!</i>

203
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,560
[ALL GROANING]

204
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:52,960
Are you ready to receive
professional training in rock?

205
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:56,630
- Have you been awake all night?
- I am so excited, I couldn't fall asleep.

206
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,100
I even took some pills
I found on the floor.

207
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,030
You took pills you found on the floor?

208
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:04,320
Uh-huh, now I'm afraid that if I stop
talking, I'll die. Isn't Mick cool?

209
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,410
I thought he'd be all like,
"I'm a rock star. Aren't I great?"

210
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:10,100
But he's just like you or me
or Jesus over there.

211
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,440
- Can I have a guitar?
- Can I have a guitar?

212
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,030
[WHISTLES]

213
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:19,070
People, if everyone's gonna pick guitar,
I'm not gonna have enough.

214
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,810
- Oh, come on.
- There's lots of other fun instruments...

215
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,440
...like bass.

216
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,830
Come on,
who'd like to be a bass player?

217
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,140
Out of my way, nerdlinger.

218
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,530
- My image.
OTTO: Get me the Strat.

219
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,080
Hand me the Strat.

220
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,600
I'm telling Mr. Jagger.

221
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:40,170
Ooh, "I'm telling Mr. Jagger."

222
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,780
<i>[LENNY KRAVITZ'S "ARE YOU</i>
<i>GONNA GO MY WAY?" PLAYING]</i>

223
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,940
The clothes you wear on stage should
be a defiant statement of individuality.

224
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,460
HOMER:
Like this, Mr. Kravitz?

225
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,790
God, no.

226
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:55,230
May we talk about, uh, accentuating
the masculine area?

227
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,390
Did you hear that, people?
Apu asked about crotch stuffing.

228
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:01,130
Now, I don't do it.
Kenny Loggins does.

229
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,040
I trusted you!

230
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:03,110
I trusted you!

231
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,650
[SOBBING]

232
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,480
[GUITAR PLAYING]

233
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,070
Now, a guitar has many,
many nicknames.

234
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:14,570
An ax, a gitbox...
Well, I guess that's it.

235
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,090
Anyway, we're gonna start
with the fundamentals.

236
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,170
Playing a burning guitar
with your teeth.

237
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,650
All right, fire.

238
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,440
- Mr. Seltzer?
- Setzer.

239
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,920
No, I think it's Seltzer.

240
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:25,120
[GRUNTS]

241
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,160
- What is it, Homer?
- I came up with a stage move...

242
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,790
...I feel is very cool.

243
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,390
[GRUNTING]

244
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:33,500
[SINGING]
<i>Baby, baby, baby, baby</i>

245
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,520
We've gotta start using
a cheaper oatmeal.

246
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,430
HOMER:
Sorry, Mick!

247
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,550
Simpson!

248
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,300
["SHE'S SO COLD"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

249
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,610
Okay, strut, strut, strut...

250
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:50,660
...strut, strut, spin, and rooster.

251
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,600
Look, everyone, Homer's got it.

252
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,350
[SINGING] <i>I'm so hot for me</i>
<i>I'm so hot for me</i>

253
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,350
<i>I'm so cold</i>

254
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,230
Okay, now schoolmarm.

255
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:02,500
<i>I'm the burning fire</i>

256
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,610
<i>I'm the bleeding volcano</i>

257
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,660
Everybody's naughty...

258
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,870
...and freeze finish.

259
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,230
WIGGUM:
Ow.

260
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,760
No matter where you are...

261
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:14,510
...always say it's the wildest town
in the whole damn world.

262
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,530
When you said it in Springfield last year,
you didn't mean it?

263
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:21,580
Yeah, sure I did. But only because
Springfield really is the wildest town...

264
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,750
...in the whole damn world.

265
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,910
- Yes, I knew it. I knew it.
- Springfield!

266
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,710
[GUITAR PLAYING]

267
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:30,180
Lyrics are the hardest part
of songwriting.

268
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,030
When you come up with something
meaningful and heartfelt...

269
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,810
- Boring.
- Will you stop saying that?

270
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,180
Rock stars are supposed
to be about drinking...

271
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:40,180
...and getting drunk and boozing it up.

272
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,390
Girls that have legs
and know how to use them.

273
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,520
And why I can't drive 55.

274
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,570
You just want mindless generic rock?

275
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,370
Precisely.

276
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,440
[GROANS]

277
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:56,870
[SINGING] <i>See that drunk girl</i>
<i>Speeding down the street?</i>

278
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,340
ALL:
Yeah!

279
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:01,380
<i>She's worried about the state</i>
<i>Of public schools</i>

280
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,400
[ALL BOOING]

281
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,660
<i>She likes to party,
she likes to rock</i>

282
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,350
ALL:
Yeah!

283
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:10,280
<i>She prays that our schools</i>
<i>Don't run out of chalk</i>

284
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:11,960
[ALL BOOING]

285
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,650
Getting away from the gig
can be a matter of life and death.

286
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,970
So you gotta be in
great physical shape.

287
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,340
Okay, follow me.

288
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,050
[AUDIENCE CHEERING
OVER SPEAKERS]

289
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,390
- Paparazzi to the left.
- I got them.

290
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,030
[GRUNTING]

291
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:38,030
I'm entitled to a private life.
I'm not a role model and so forth.

292
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,060
Good, Homer. Now, just past
the groupies and we're home.

293
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,810
WOMAN [ON RECORDING]:
<i>I love you. Please sleep with us.</i>

294
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,210
They're bloody cardboard.

295
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,730
We know.

296
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,830
[SINGING]
<i>You ain't never caught a rabbit</i>

297
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:58,590
<i>And you ain't no friend of mine</i>

298
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:06,410
- Yeah!
ALL: Aah!

299
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,890
Well, what do you think?

300
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,000
Uh, you rock, Homer.

301
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:14,920
Really?
You really think I'm better than you?

302
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,400
That was great, Homie.

303
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:20,120
- What the hell are you doing here?
- Camp is over, Homer.

304
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:22,850
- It's been a week already?
- I'm glad you had fun.

305
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,750
- But it's time to come home.
- Your mother's right, Homer.

306
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,880
- Gotta get back to the real world.
- We've all gotta get home.

307
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,810
My lawn's not gonna mow itself.

308
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,760
And I've gotta put up
the storm windows. Winter's coming.

309
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,090
HOMER:
Wait. Don't go.

310
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:41,530
I wanna keep on rocking.
Come on, guys. A-one, a-two...

311
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,350
I'll take that.

312
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,560
No!

313
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:45,960
[SOBBING]

314
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,580
It came with a pick.

315
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,360
[GROANS]

316
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,020
Come on, Dad.

317
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:59,350
No! No! I won't go. You can't make me!

318
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,490
- You knew this day was coming.
- I knew nothing.

319
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,050
Ugh, stop kicking me, Dad.

320
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,740
Never.

321
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,770
[SOBS]

322
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,040
My dream has been shattered
into shards of a broken dream.

323
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:14,290
I was so close to being a rock star...

324
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,860
...but now,
there's a chance it might not happen.

325
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:21,430
I'll just have to settle
for being a fat, bald, fat nothing.

326
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,600
Finally. Can we go now?

327
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:28,380
Now, before I lock the door,
do you have to go to the bathroom?

328
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:31,250
No, I'm fine.

329
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,410
Ugh, I'm so despondent.

330
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:37,730
Cheer up, Homer.
It's only rock 'n' roll camp.

331
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,330
But I like it.

332
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,980
[SOBBING]

333
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,220
Tell you what, we're doing a benefit gig
before we leave.

334
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:48,340
How would you like to join us
on-stage?

335
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,740
- For serious?
- For serious, Homer.

336
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,600
Can I have 40 guest passes?

337
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:58,050
Woo-hoo!

338
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,450
Wow, all access.

339
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:04,800
All access.

340
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,460
Ooh, good thing it's laminated.
Ha-ha-ha.

341
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,260
[GRUNTS]

342
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,370
- Sir, you can't...
- All access.

343
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:12,630
Oh, sorry.

344
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:17,690
[HUMMING]

345
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,460
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

346
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,450
HOMER: All access.
WOMAN 1: Ooh.

347
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,000
- Nice.
WOMAN 2: You rock.

348
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,970
[CHATTERING]

349
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:28,250
Wow, Homer. I ain't had front row
seats since my Moonie wedding.

350
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:31,120
After the show, you can come backstage
for pizza and pop.

351
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,510
- Yes!
- All right!

352
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,700
Now, that's a winning combination.

353
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,220
Here you go. Front and center.

354
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,120
I'm so proud of you, Homie.

355
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:44,280
It's like you're Kid Rock
and I'm Pamela Anderson Lee Rock.

356
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,680
[CROWD CHEERING]

357
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:49,370
Ooh, gotta run. Enjoy the show.

358
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,320
Okay, let's see the eyes.

359
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,970
Now the fire.

360
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:04,080
Thanks, mate.

361
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:07,520
- Couldn't you find a fuel-efficient Satan?
- Don't you have a crotch to stuff?

362
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,140
Evening, fellow rockers.

363
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,940
There you are. Thought we were
going to go on without you.

364
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,290
I'm ready. Just give me a guitar.
How many solos should I do? Four.

365
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,470
I'll do four.

366
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:22,540
Uh, Homer, you didn't think
you were gonna be playing with...?

367
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:23,960
[GASPS]

368
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,450
My official tour jacket. Lookit...

369
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:29,560
Wait. You misspelled "guitar hero."

370
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,260
Look, sorry if there's been
a misunderstanding, Homer.

371
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,690
We really just need you
to tap the mikes and say:

372
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:37,650
- "Test, test."
- Can't you do it?

373
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:40,990
Oh.

374
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,460
Okay. So I'll, uh...

375
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,650
Okay.

376
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,630
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

377
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,010
- Look, there's Dad!
- Woo-hoo! Yay, Homer!

378
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,270
I'm his groupie, ha, ha.

379
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,120
Am I saying that right? Groupie?

380
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:00,540
- Yeah!
WOMAN: Yeah, Homer!

381
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,880
CARL: You're the man, Homer!
You're the man!

382
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:04,790
LENNY:
You rock the house! Let's go, Homer!

383
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,740
MOE:
It's go time! It's go time!

384
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,600
Test. Test.

385
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,680
Why is he performing
the duties of a roadie?

386
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,810
Am I saying that right? Roadie?

387
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,000
Test, test. Check, check.

388
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:20,140
- Hey, he's not rocking out at all.
- Test.

389
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,530
Test. Test.

390
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,280
[SINGING]
<i>You're testing my love for you</i>

391
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:27,850
<i>Check, check</i>
<i>You're checking to see if I'm true</i>

392
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:29,800
[CROWD CHEERING]

393
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,240
<i>Test one, test two</i>
<i>Test three, test four</i>

394
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,680
<i>You test me like the water</i>
<i>In El Salvador</i>

395
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,550
- Whoa, El Salvador!
- What's all this then?

396
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:39,410
He's stealing the show from us.

397
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,760
JAGGER:
Not on my shift.

398
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,110
Let's rock 'n' roll.

399
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:47,360
[ALL CHEERING]

400
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,260
[SINGING]
<i>Baby, baby, baby, baby, baby</i>

401
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,080
Uh-oh.

402
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,980
[SCREAMS]

403
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,830
No!

404
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,940
[CROWD CHEERING]

405
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,940
Oh, yeah. It's good to see the spectacle
back in rock.

406
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,010
[ALL SCREAMING]

407
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,450
Did you know
it was gonna turn into a riot, Dad?

408
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:21,860
Oh, yeah.

409
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,800
When you've been in as many as I have,
you can sense them coming.

410
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:29,150
- Did they ever find Tom Petty's toe?
- What am I, the lost and found?

411
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:32,750
There's no excuse
for our horrible behavior tonight, Homer.

412
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,890
We acted like a bunch
of angry young men.

413
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:37,350
Rock 'n' roll is supposed to be
about peace and love.

414
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:40,580
I hope you won't judge the entire
Brian Setzer Orchestra by my actions.

415
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,620
What we're trying to say,
Homer, is we're sorry.

416
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:46,370
By the way, I don't suppose
any of you have seen my, um...?

417
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,320
- No. Sorry.
- Oh.

418
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:51,840
There's no need for apologies, guys.
You're rock stars.

419
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:54,580
You're supposed to be reckless
and destructive...

420
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:58,520
...and be celebrated for behavior
that would land normal people in jail.

421
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,570
That's what I told them, Homer.

422
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,850
Just the same,
we'd like to make it up to you.

423
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:06,160
We're doing a gig tomorrow
to benefit the victims of tonight's gig.

424
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,370
We'd consider it an honor
if you join us.

425
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,520
Well, you're very sweet, Mick.

426
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:14,700
But the only rocking I wanna do
is in my living-room chair...

427
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,320
...surrounded by the world's
greatest backup group, my family.

428
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:19,320
...surrounded by the world's
greatest backup group, my family.

429
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,360
[OVER RADIO]
<i>There goes the last DJ</i>

430
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,350
Are you sure you don't miss hanging out
with your rock-star friends, Dad?

431
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,850
No, I got something
to remember them by.

432
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:30,300
[LAUGHS]

433
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:32,500
- Have fun at school, kids.
- Later, Homer.

434
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,840
Mr. Simpson,
this zone is for school buses only.

435
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,440
[SCREAMS]

436
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:39,630
[ALL LAUGHING]

437
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,330
Rock 'n' roll! Woo-hoo.

438
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,230
[KIDS CHEERING]

439
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:44,940
["RIP THIS JOINT"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKER]

440
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:46,160
<i>Papa says no</i>

441
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,360
<i>Make up you mind 'cause I gotta go</i>

442
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,550
<i>I'm gonna raise hell
at the Union Hall</i>

443
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,930
<i>Drive myself right over the wall</i>

444
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,400
<i>Rip this joint</i>
<i>Gonna save your soul</i>

445
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,560
<i>Round and round and round we go</i>

446
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,930
<i>Roll this joint</i>
<i>Gonna get down low</i>

447
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,960
<i>Start my starter</i>
<i>Gonna stop the show</i>

448
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:08,030
And I've gotta put up
the storm windows. Winter's coming.

449
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:11,970
Everybody's naughty and freeze finish.

450
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:15,590
[SINGING] <i>She likes to
party, she likes to rock</i>

451
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,040
HOMER:
Yeah!

452
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:19,640
But there's lots of other fun instruments,
like bass.

453
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:22,900
I hope you won't judge the entire
Brian Setzer Orchestra by my actions.

454
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,440
Rock 'n' roll is supposed to be
about peace and love.

455
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,950
- Who said that?
- Will you stop saying that?

456
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,880
[ALL LAUGHING]

457
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,140
JAGGER:
<i>Simpson!</i>

458
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:38,080
[English - US -SDH]